bonds have much higher yields,

00:08:57.590 --> 00:09:01.058
so the last one is the 30-year
bond.

00:09:01.058 --> 00:09:07.700
So you get the yield on every
single bond.

00:09:07.700 --> 00:09:09.734
Now what do you notice about
this picture,

00:09:09.734 --> 00:09:10.379
by the way?
 

00:09:10.379 --> 00:09:13.480
They can be very different at
different time periods,

00:09:13.480 --> 00:09:16.462
so in December 2000,
the interest rates were really

00:09:16.462 --> 00:09:17.000
high.
 

00:09:17.000 --> 00:09:18.360
The yields were 6 percent.
 

00:09:18.360 --> 00:09:19.480
I'm talking yields so far.
 

00:09:19.480 --> 00:09:20.700
We haven't talked about
interest rates.

00:09:20.700 --> 00:09:22.159
We have to figure out what the
interest rates are,

00:09:22.159 --> 00:09:23.769
but anyway, they're obviously
going to be connected.

00:09:23.769 --> 00:09:27.023
So the yields were very high in
December 2000,

00:09:27.023 --> 00:09:29.916
and they got much lower in
December 2008,

00:09:29.916 --> 00:09:32.230
and they've stayed very low.
 

00:09:32.230 --> 00:09:34.990
So why are they so low now?
 

00:09:34.990 --> 00:09:38.070
